3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit calculates AVAX/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium/discount between perpetual and spot prices. The funding fee applies only to positions held at settlement time, with rates typically ranging from -0.375% to +0.375% daily. Bybit's unified account system allows seamless hedging across spot and derivatives markets within a single account."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","AVAX","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AVAX exhibits significant funding rate volatility due to its L1 blockchain narrative and institutional interest in Avalanche ecosystem projects. High trading volumes on Bybit ensure tight spreads and reliable arbitrage execution, while AVAX's correlation with broader DeFi trends creates predictable funding rate cycles during market momentum shifts."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AVAX/USDT funding rates on Bybit have shown distinct patterns during ecosystem developments and seasonal DeFi activity. Positive funding rates often coincide with subnet launches or major partnership announcements, reaching peaks of 0.1-0.2% per 8-hour period. During bear markets, funding rates frequently turn negative as shorts dominate, creating opportunities for long arbitrage positions. The pair exhibits higher volatility during US trading hours when institutional activity peaks."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Strategy Implementation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Optimal AVAX funding arbitrage on Bybit involves monitoring rate predictions 2-4 hours before settlement to identify high-probability trades. Delta-neutral strategies work best by taking opposite positions in perpetual futures and spot markets, capturing funding payments while minimizing directional risk. Bybit's 0.02% maker fees for limit orders make this particularly cost-effective for larger position sizes. Consider using Bybit's API for automated rate monitoring and position management."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AVAX's price volatility can exceed funding gains if positions aren't properly hedged, especially during network upgrades or major announcements. Bybit's mark price mechanism helps prevent manipulation but sudden liquidity gaps can still occur during extreme moves. Monitor AVAX staking rewards and unlock schedules as they can influence perpetual demand and funding dynamics. Set strict position limits as AVAX can experience 20%+ daily moves during high volatility periods."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Bybit settle AVAX/USDT funding rates?","answer":"Bybit settles AVAX/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. You only pay or receive funding if you hold positions at these exact settlement times."},{"question":"What's the typical funding rate range for AVAX on Bybit?","answer":"AVAX funding rates on Bybit typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% per 8-hour period during normal market conditions. During major AVAX ecosystem events or extreme market moves, rates can reach the daily limits of ±0.375%."},{"question":"Can I hedge AVAX perpetuals with spot on the same Bybit account?","answer":"Yes, Bybit's unified account allows you to hedge AVAX perpetual positions with AVAX spot holdings seamlessly. This enables delta-neutral funding rate arbitrage without transferring funds between different account types."},{"question":"How does AVAX subnet activity affect funding rates on Bybit?","answer":"Major subnet launches or Avalanche ecosystem developments typically drive increased long interest in AVAX perpetuals, pushing funding rates positive. Monitor Avalanche's official announcements and subnet roadmaps to anticipate potential funding rate spikes."}]}]
